description.narrative: Strategies to address cross-cutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Learning Outcomes, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas (Covid), Supply And Logistics. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children in development and humanitarian settings.

description.narrative: UNICEF Pacific MCO has placed continued emphasis on cross-cutting support to programming. UNICEF work on ECD has resulted in the endorsement of the Pacific Regional Council for ECD and renewed commitment from 15 countries to strengthening ECD programming as stipulated in the Pasifika Call for Action on ECD. C4D support during the measles outbreak in Samoa has demonstrated its unique position and capacity to deliver multiple and innovative approaches that works in the context of the Pacific, both in the development and humanitarian setting. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
